IMM_ADMIN.name: IMM_ADMIN
IMM_ADMIN.description: The IMM_ADMIN table contains information about the immunization administered. The rows included in this table are items from DXR (Document) masterfile which include information on type of immunization, administration date, administered dose, administration route, administration site, immunization manufacturer, immunization lot number, administered by, visit date, deferral reason, administration notes, administration location, administration status, administered amount, administered unit, contact serial number of the DXR record that owns the immunization instance and a unique reference identifier to identify a specific instance of an immunization.

columns.name: DOCUMENT_ID
columns.description: The unique identifier for the document record.

columns.name: CONTACT_DATE_REAL
columns.description: A unique contact date in decimal format. The integer portion of the number indicates the date of contact. The digits after the decimal distinguish different contacts on the same date and are unique for each contact on that date. For example, .00 is the first/only contact, .01 is the second contact, etc.

columns.name: LINE
columns.description: The line number for the information associated with this contact. Multiple pieces of information can be associated with this contact.

columns.name: CONTACT_DATE
columns.description: The date of this contact in calendar format.

columns.name: IMM_TYPE_FREE_TEXT
columns.description: The immunization type information for the administered immunization as free text.

columns.name: IMM_ROUTE_C_NAME
columns.description: The immunization administration route category ID.

columns.name: IMM_SITE_C_NAME
columns.description: The immunization administration site category ID.

columns.name: IMM_MANUFACTURER_C_NAME
columns.description: The immunization administered manufacturer category ID.

columns.name: IMM_GIVEN_BY_FT
columns.description: The immunization given by information for the administered immunization as free text.

columns.name: IMM_NOTES_RAW_DATA
columns.description: Free text immunization notes from the immunization administration.

columns.name: IMM_REFERENCE_ID
columns.description: This item stores a unique reference identifier to identify a specific instance of an immunization.
